  "prompt": "What are some of the biggest flaws of Quora?",
  "response": "Here are some commonly cited flaws of Quora:\n\n1. Low-quality or repetitive answers\n- Many answers lack depth or are overly generic\n- Same questions get asked repeatedly\n- High volume of low-effort responses\n\n2. Moderation and content issues\n- Inconsistent moderation\n- Potential for bias in content selection\n- Some users feel certain viewpoints are suppressed\n\n3. User experience problems\n- Aggressive push notifications\n- Paywalls/restrictions on viewing content\n- Cluttered interface\n\n4. Answer ranking system\n- Not always the most qualified people get top answers\n- Popularity sometimes trumps expertise\n- Potential for gaming the ranking system\n\n5. Privacy concerns\n- Requires detailed personal profile\n- Can inadvertently reveal personal information\n- Complex privacy settings\n\n6. Spam and self-promotion\n- Some users use platform for marketing\n- Excessive cross-linking to external content\n- Frequent promotional answers\n\n7. Community dynamics\n- Can feel elitist or cliquish\n- Potential for toxic interactions\n- Some users feel unfairly treated by moderators\n\n8. Technical limitations\n- Search function can be inefficient\n- Mobile app performance issues\n- Formatting and editing constraints\n\nThese criticisms are based on user experiences and may vary individually.",
